originalText.text: The dishes I have had from Asia Express have all been delicious. I have been a customer for many years, going back to their previous location. The food is also reasonably priced & the owner & his wife are pleasant & hardworking. I do not understand the reviews that say negative things about the food. It is not an experience I have ever had there!

originalText.text: Asia Express is great fast food. The food is served quickly and piping hot. The ingredients are fresh and flavorful. The staff took care of my allergies, and made a big effort to make sure I got what I wanted. I wish the restaurant was a little bigger so staying to eat would be a bit more convenient, so I suggest take out. Will definitely come back, as the menu is pretty big and the location is quite convenient for me.

originalText.text: The food is disgusting, it’s always “warm” never “hot” I caught the lady that works there handling food wit NO GLOVES on and putting them into the deep fryer, So of course I wasn’t gonna sit there and let that go down I called her out on it she was really upset about it and was arguing with me. But we all know who has the last laugh... better business bureau!

originalText.text:
Worst tastless Chinese food I ever ate.  I still have no clue why I ate it.
I'm thinking I was starving and had smothered it with my favorite salad dressing.  I order something simple friend rice and 1/2 of a fried chicken.
First off the half of chicken was not whole it was chopped up beyond recognition.  You could not tell what was a breast thigh.  I did recognize a drum stick but when I picked it up the other side was missing.   Do not waste your money.  Go elsewhere!!!

originalText.text: Ordered from here a few times over the past year. Both in-person and delivery. Never had an issue. I'm a big General Tso's chicken fan and it has tasted great every single time.
